VIM keys:

ACTION + LOCATION + CONTEXT

Mode:
    ESC/CTRL+[ : command mode
    
    
Move:
    h : left
    j : down
    k : up 
    l : right
    w : next word
    b:  back a word
    e : end of word / next word
    b : beginning of word / next word
    0 : beginning of line
    $ : end of line
    gg : begining of file
    G : end of file
    :/G + num : line num
    + : beginning of next line
    - beginning of previous line
    CTRL + u : page up
    CTRL + d : page down
    z then RETURN : current line goes to top of screen
    CTRL + w : switch between windows

Edit :
    i : insert text before cursor
    a : append text after cursor
    I : insert text at beginning of line
    A : insert text at end of line
    x : delete under cursor
    X : delete left of cursor
    r : replace under cursor
    C : replace characters on line
    c : change + other movement characters
    d : delete + other movement characters
        w : word
        d : line
    o : insert line
    cit: change insert tags
    ci{: change inside curly braces
    ci": change inside "


Cut'n'Paste
    v: visual mode
    Shift + v : visual line mode
    y: yank (or can use delete)
    yy: yank entire line
    p : paste


Indenting
    >> : indent
    << : unindent
    N<< or N>> : for the next N lines
    gg=G: autoindent entire file
    N== : autoindent N lines

Search:
    f : character search
    * : find next of word under cursor
    # : find previous of work under cursor
    / : search for text/reg-exp
        n for next
    % : matching parenthesis

Replace:
   :%s/before/after/gc : search whole doc and confirm all

Buffers:
    edit xxx : open new buffer
    bd : delete existing buffer


Commands:
    . : repeat
    u : undo
    CTRL+R : redo


Program:
    :q : quit
    :w : save


